						<div class="fac_des"><div class="about_fac"><span id="spec">Education:</span> Ph.D. (Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur)<br/><span id="spec">Email:</span> ddas<br/><span id="spec">Description:</span> Dr. Debabrata Das is serving as Dean &ndash; Academic and R&amp;D as well as Professor and Hewlett Packard Chair at IIIT-Bangalore (IIIT-B). Before joining IIIT-B, he had served at G S Sanyal School of Telecommunication at IIT Kharagpur and later at Kirana Networks in New Jersey, USA. He is Principal Investigator (PI) of a project from Department of Electronics and Information Technology, Government of India on Green Broadband Wireless Network and Co-PI of a project from Microsoft on TVWS. He was PI of sponsored projects from Hewlett Packard, Motorola Research, Intel, GoI as well as Nokia on areas of IMS and Broadband Wireless MAC/QoS/Energy-saving. His main areas of research interest are Wireless Access Network&#39;s MAC, QoS, Power saving and IP Multimedia Subsystems. His areas of teaching interest are, Wireless Access Network, Mobile Computing with IMS, IoT and Internetworking. He has more than 75 peer reviewed papers in different journals and International conferences. He and his wireless network team had contributed three ideas to IEEE 802.16m Broadband Wireless Standard. Dr. Das received his Ph.D. degree from the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur (IIT Kharagpur). </div></div>
